title: Mooch Goes to Hollywood (1974, Comedy film) Vincent Price, James Darren

sources.title: Mooch Goes to Hollywood (1974, Comedy film) Vincent Price, James Darren
sources.description:
A mischievous dog named Mooch sneaks onto a bus to Hollywood in search of stardom and tries to make it in show business.  Narrated by Zsa Zsa Gabor, the film captures the essence of 1970s entertainment industry.

Director: Richard Erdman
Writers: Jerry Devine, Jim Backus
Main Cast: Vincent Price, James Darren, Jill St. John 
Narrators: Richard Burton, Zsa Zsa Gabor
Genres: Classics, Comedy, Family


00:00 Full Movie (with subtitles).
07:01 Mooch, a dog, embarks on a Hollywood adventure with Mr. Price, encountering challenges and rejection along the way.
18:06 A comedic journey of a dog named Sunshine in Hollywood, involving James Darren and a doctor's mix-up.
30:34 Mooch navigates Hollywood with the help of industry insiders, leading to unexpected success and recognition.
43:54 A dog named Mooch ventures into Hollywood, encountering various celebrities and experiencing the ups and downs of show business.
